{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3000,"text":"I'm going to talk about a technology that we're developing at Oxford now,"},{"time":7000,"text":"that we think is going to change the way that"},{"time":10000,"text":"computer games and Hollywood movies are being made."},{"time":14000,"text":"That technology is simulating humans."},{"time":17000,"text":"It's simulated humans with a simulated body"},{"time":20000,"text":"and a simulated nervous system to control that body."},{"time":24000,"text":"Now, before I talk more about that technology,"},{"time":27000,"text":"let's have a quick look at what human characters look like"},{"time":30000,"text":"at the moment in computer games."},{"time":33000,"text":"This is a clip from a game called \"Grand Theft Auto 3.\""},{"time":36000,"text":"We already saw that briefly yesterday."},{"time":38000,"text":"And what you can see is -- it is actually a very good game."},{"time":41000,"text":"It's one of the most successful games of all time."},{"time":44000,"text":"But what you'll see is that all the animations in this game are very repetitive."},{"time":48000,"text":"They pretty much look the same."},{"time":50000,"text":"I've made him run into a wall here, over and over again."},{"time":53000,"text":"And you can see he looks always the same."},{"time":55000,"text":"The reason for that is that these characters"},{"time":58000,"text":"are actually not real characters."},{"time":60000,"text":"They are a graphical visualization of a character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"To produce these animations, an animator at a studio has to anticipate"},{"time":69000,"text":"what's going to happen in the actual game,"},{"time":72000,"text":"and then has to animate that particular sequence."},{"time":75000,"text":"So, he or she sits down, animates it, and tries to anticipate what's going to happen,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and then these particular animations are just played back"},{"time":82000,"text":"at appropriate times in the computer game."},{"time":85000,"text":"Now, the result of that is that you can't have real interactivity."},{"time":90000,"text":"All you have is animations that are played back"},{"time":93000,"text":"at more or less the appropriate times."},{"time":95000,"text":"It also means that games aren't really going to be as surprising as they could be,"},{"time":100000,"text":"because you only get out of it, at least in terms of the character,"},{"time":103000,"text":"what you actually put into it."},{"time":105000,"text":"There's no real emergence there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"And thirdly, as I said, most of the animations are very repetitive because of that."},{"time":111000,"text":"Now, the only way to get around that"},{"time":113000,"text":"is to actually simulate the human body"},{"time":115000,"text":"and to simulate that bit of the nervous system of the brain that controls that body."},{"time":120000,"text":"And maybe, if I could have you for a quick demonstration"},{"time":123000,"text":"to show what the difference is --"},{"time":125000,"text":"because, I mean, it's very, very trivial."},{"time":129000,"text":"If I push Chris a bit, like this, for example, he'll react to it."},{"time":132000,"text":"If I push him from a different angle, he'll react to it differently,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and that's because he has a physical body,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and because he has the motor skills to control that body."},{"time":140000,"text":"It's a very trivial thing."},{"time":142000,"text":"It's not something you get in computer games at the moment, at all."},{"time":144000,"text":"Thank you very much. Chris Anderson: That's it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"Torsten Reil: That's it, yes."},{"time":148000,"text":"So, that's what we're trying to simulate --"},{"time":149000,"text":"not Chris specifically, I should say, but humans in general."},{"time":154000,"text":"Now, we started working on this a while ago at Oxford University,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and we tried to start very simply."},{"time":161000,"text":"What we tried to do was teach a stick figure how to walk."},{"time":164000,"text":"That stick figure is physically stimulated. You can see it here on the screen."},{"time":167000,"text":"So, it's subject to gravity, has joints, etc."},{"time":170000,"text":"If you just run the simulation, it will just collapse, like this."},{"time":173000,"text":"The tricky bit is now to put an AI controller in it"},{"time":177000,"text":"that actually makes it work."},{"time":179000,"text":"And for that, we use the neural network, which we based on"},{"time":182000,"text":"that part of the nervous system that we have in our spine"},{"time":184000,"text":"that controls walking in humans."},{"time":186000,"text":"It's called the central pattern generator."},{"time":188000,"text":"So, we simulated that as well, and then the really tricky bit"},{"time":191000,"text":"is to teach that network how to walk."},{"time":193000,"text":"For that we used artificial evolution -- genetic algorithms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"We heard about those already yesterday,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and I suppose that most of you are familiar with that already."},{"time":202000,"text":"But, just briefly, the concept is that"},{"time":204000,"text":"you create a large number of different individuals --"},{"time":207000,"text":"neural networks, in this case --"},{"time":209000,"text":"all of which are random at the beginning."},{"time":211000,"text":"You hook these up -- in this case, to the virtual muscles"},{"time":213000,"text":"of that two-legged creature here --"},{"time":216000,"text":"and hope that it does something interesting."},{"time":219000,"text":"At the beginning, they're all going to be very boring."},{"time":221000,"text":"Most of them won't move at all,"},{"time":223000,"text":"but some of them might make a tiny step."},{"time":225000,"text":"Those are then selected by the algorithm,"},{"time":227000,"text":"reproduced with mutation and recombinations to introduce sex as well."},{"time":231000,"text":"And you repeat that process over and over again,"},{"time":233000,"text":"until you have something that walks --"},{"time":235000,"text":"in this case, in a straight line, like this."},{"time":237000,"text":"So that was the idea behind this."},{"time":239000,"text":"When we started this, I set up the simulation one evening."},{"time":242000,"text":"It took about three to four hours to run the simulation."},{"time":245000,"text":"I got up the next morning, went to the computer and looked at the results,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and was hoping for something that walked in a straight line,"},{"time":252000,"text":"like I've just demonstrated,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and this is what I got instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"So, it was back to the drawing board for us."},{"time":270000,"text":"We did get it to work eventually,"},{"time":273000,"text":"after tweaking a bit here and there."},{"time":275000,"text":"And this is an example of a successful evolutionary run."},{"time":278000,"text":"So, what you'll see in a moment is a very simple biped"},{"time":281000,"text":"that's learning how to walk using artificial evolution."},{"time":284000,"text":"At the beginning, it can't walk at all,"},{"time":286000,"text":"but it will get better and better over time."},{"time":290000,"text":"So, this is the one that can't walk at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Now, after five generations of applying evolutionary process,"},{"time":302000,"text":"the genetic algorithm is getting a tiny bit better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"Generation 10 and it'll take a few steps more --"},{"time":319000,"text":"still not quite there."},{"time":322000,"text":"But now, after generation 20, it actually walks in a straight line without falling over."},{"time":328000,"text":"That was the real breakthrough for us."},{"time":331000,"text":"It was, academically, quite a challenging project,"},{"time":334000,"text":"and once we had reached that stage, we were quite confident"},{"time":337000,"text":"that we could try and do other things as well with this approach --"},{"time":340000,"text":"actually simulating the body"},{"time":342000,"text":"and simulating that part of the nervous system that controls it."},{"time":345000,"text":"Now, at this stage, it also became clear that this could be very exciting"},{"time":348000,"text":"for things like computer games or online worlds."},{"time":351000,"text":"What you see here is the character standing there,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and there's an obstacle that we put in its way."},{"time":355000,"text":"And what you see is, it's going to fall over the obstacle."},{"time":360000,"text":"Now, the interesting bit is, if I move the obstacle a tiny bit to the right,"},{"time":363000,"text":"which is what I'm doing now, here,"},{"time":365000,"text":"it will fall over it in a completely different way."},{"time":372000,"text":"And again, if you move the obstacle a tiny bit, it'll again fall differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"Now, what you see, by the way, at the top there,"},{"time":381000,"text":"are some of the neural activations being fed into the virtual muscles."},{"time":384000,"text":"Okay. That's the video. Thanks."},{"time":386000,"text":"Now, this might look kind of trivial, but it's actually very important"},{"time":389000,"text":"because this is not something you get at the moment"},{"time":391000,"text":"in any interactive or any virtual worlds."},{"time":396000,"text":"Now, at this stage, we decided to start a company and move this further,"},{"time":399000,"text":"because obviously this was just a very simple, blocky biped."},{"time":402000,"text":"What we really wanted was a full human body."},{"time":404000,"text":"So we started the company."},{"time":405000,"text":"We hired a team of physicists, software engineers and biologists"},{"time":410000,"text":"to work on this, and the first thing we had to work on"},{"time":413000,"text":"was to create the human body, basically."},{"time":417000,"text":"It's got to be relatively fast, so you can run it on a normal machine,"},{"time":420000,"text":"but it's got to be accurate enough, so it looks good enough, basically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"So we put quite a bit of biomechanical knowledge into this thing,"},{"time":426000,"text":"and tried to make it as realistic as possible."},{"time":430000,"text":"What you see here on the screen right now"},{"time":432000,"text":"is a very simple visualization of that body."},{"time":434000,"text":"I should add that it's very simple to add things like hair, clothes, etc.,"},{"time":438000,"text":"but what we've done here is use a very simple visualization,"},{"time":441000,"text":"so you can concentrate on the movement."},{"time":443000,"text":"Now, what I'm going to do right now, in a moment,"},{"time":446000,"text":"is just push this character a tiny bit and we'll see what happens."},{"time":454000,"text":"Nothing really interesting, basically."},{"time":456000,"text":"It falls over, but it falls over like a rag doll, basically."},{"time":459000,"text":"The reason for that is that there's no intelligence in it."},{"time":462000,"text":"It becomes interesting when you put artificial intelligence into it."},{"time":466000,"text":"So, this character now has motor skills in the upper body --"},{"time":470000,"text":"nothing in the legs yet, in this particular one."},{"time":472000,"text":"But what it will do -- I'm going to push it again."},{"time":475000,"text":"It will realize autonomously that it's being pushed."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's going to stick out its hands."},{"time":479000,"text":"It's going to turn around into the fall, and try and catch the fall."},{"time":488000,"text":"So that's what you see here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Now, it gets really interesting"},{"time":492000,"text":"if you then add the AI for the lower part of the body as well."},{"time":496000,"text":"So here, we've got the same character."},{"time":498000,"text":"I'm going to push it a bit harder now,"},{"time":500000,"text":"harder than I just pushed Chris."},{"time":502000,"text":"But what you'll see is -- it's going to receive a push now from the left."},{"time":509000,"text":"What you see is it takes steps backwards,"},{"time":511000,"text":"it tries to counter-balance,"},{"time":513000,"text":"it tries to look at the place where it thinks it's going to land."},{"time":517000,"text":"I'll show you this again."},{"time":519000,"text":"And then, finally hits the floor."},{"time":523000,"text":"Now, this becomes really exciting"},{"time":526000,"text":"when you push that character in different directions, again, just as I've done."},{"time":531000,"text":"That's something that you cannot do right now."},{"time":535000,"text":"At the moment, you only have empty computer graphics in games."},{"time":538000,"text":"What this is now is a real simulation. That's what I want to show you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"So, here's the same character with the same behavior I've just shown you,"},{"time":544000,"text":"but now I'm just going to push it from different directions."},{"time":546000,"text":"First, starting with a push from the right."},{"time":551000,"text":"This is all slow motion, by the way, so we can see what's going on."},{"time":554000,"text":"Now, the angle will have changed a tiny bit,"},{"time":557000,"text":"so you can see that the reaction is different."},{"time":561000,"text":"Again, a push, now this time from the front."},{"time":565000,"text":"And you see it falls differently."},{"time":567000,"text":"And now from the left --"},{"time":571000,"text":"and it falls differently."},{"time":573000,"text":"That was really exciting for us to see that."},{"time":575000,"text":"That was the first time we've seen that."},{"time":577000,"text":"This is the first time the public sees this as well,"},{"time":579000,"text":"because we have been in stealth mode."},{"time":581000,"text":"I haven't shown this to anybody yet."},{"time":583000,"text":"Now, just a fun thing:"},{"time":585000,"text":"what happens if you put that character --"},{"time":587000,"text":"this is now a wooden version of it, but it's got the same AI in it --"},{"time":589000,"text":"but if you put that character on a slippery surface, like ice."},{"time":591000,"text":"We just did that for a laugh, just to see what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"And this is what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603000,"text":"It's nothing we had to do about this."},{"time":605000,"text":"We just took this character that I just talked about,"},{"time":607000,"text":"put it on a slippery surface, and this is what you get out of it."},{"time":610000,"text":"And that's a really fascinating thing about this approach."},{"time":614000,"text":"Now, when we went to film studios and games developers"},{"time":617000,"text":"and showed them that technology, we got a very good response."},{"time":620000,"text":"And what they said was, the first thing they need immediately is virtual stuntmen."},{"time":624000,"text":"Because stunts are obviously very dangerous, they're very expensive,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and there are a lot of stunt scenes that you cannot do, obviously,"},{"time":630000,"text":"because you can't really allow the stuntman to be seriously hurt."},{"time":633000,"text":"So, they wanted to have a digital version of a stuntman"},{"time":636000,"text":"and that's what we've been working on for the past few months."},{"time":638000,"text":"And that's our first product that we're going to release in a couple of weeks."},{"time":643000,"text":"So, here are just a few very simple scenes of the guy just being kicked."},{"time":648000,"text":"That's what people want. That's what we're giving them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"You can see, it's always reacting."},{"time":659000,"text":"This is not a dead body. This is a body who basically, in this particular case,"},{"time":663000,"text":"feels the force and tries to protect its head."},{"time":665000,"text":"Only, I think it's quite a big blow again."},{"time":667000,"text":"You feel kind of sorry for that thing,"},{"time":669000,"text":"and we've seen it so many times now that"},{"time":671000,"text":"we don't really care any more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674000,"text":"There are much worse videos than this, by the way, which I have taken out, but ..."},{"time":679000,"text":"Now, here's another one."},{"time":681000,"text":"What people wanted as a behavior was to have an explosion,"},{"time":685000,"text":"a strong force applied to the character,"},{"time":687000,"text":"and have the character react to it in midair."},{"time":689000,"text":"So that you don't have a character that looks limp,"},{"time":691000,"text":"but actually a character that you can use in an action film straight away,"},{"time":694000,"text":"that looks kind of alive in midair as well."},{"time":696000,"text":"So this character is going to be hit by a force,"},{"time":698000,"text":"it's going to realize it's in the air,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and it's going to try and, well,"},{"time":703000,"text":"stick out its arm in the direction where it's landing."},{"time":707000,"text":"That's one angle; here's another angle."},{"time":710000,"text":"We now think that the realism we're achieving with this"},{"time":712000,"text":"is good enough to be used in films."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"And let's just have a look at a slightly different visualization."},{"time":717000,"text":"This is something I just got last night"},{"time":719000,"text":"from an animation studio in London, who are using our software"},{"time":722000,"text":"and experimenting with it right now."},{"time":724000,"text":"So this is exactly the same behavior that you saw,"},{"time":727000,"text":"but in a slightly better rendered version."},{"time":731000,"text":"So if you look at the character carefully,"},{"time":734000,"text":"you see there are lots of body movements going on,"},{"time":736000,"text":"none of which you have to animate like in the old days."},{"time":738000,"text":"Animators had to actually animate them."},{"time":740000,"text":"This is all happening automatically in the simulation."},{"time":742000,"text":"This is a slightly different angle,"},{"time":747000,"text":"and again a slow motion version of this."},{"time":749000,"text":"This is incredibly quick. This is happening in real time."},{"time":753000,"text":"You can run this simulation in real time, in front of your eyes,"},{"time":755000,"text":"change it, if you want to, and you get the animation straight out of it."},{"time":758000,"text":"At the moment, doing something like this by hand"},{"time":760000,"text":"would take you probably a couple of days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"This is another behavior they requested."},{"time":766000,"text":"I'm not quite sure why, but we've done it anyway."},{"time":768000,"text":"It's a very simple behavior that shows you the power of this approach."},{"time":770000,"text":"In this case, the character's hands"},{"time":772000,"text":"are fixed to a particular point in space,"},{"time":774000,"text":"and all we've told the character to do is to struggle."},{"time":777000,"text":"And it looks organic. It looks realistic."},{"time":780000,"text":"You feel kind of sorry for the guy."},{"time":782000,"text":"It's even worse -- and that is another video I just got last night --"},{"time":785000,"text":"if you render that a bit more realistically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"Now, I'm showing this to you just to show you"},{"time":793000,"text":"how organic it actually can feel, how realistic it can look."},{"time":795000,"text":"And this is all a physical simulation of the body,"},{"time":798000,"text":"using AI to drive virtual muscles in that body."},{"time":803000,"text":"Now, one thing which we did for a laugh was"},{"time":806000,"text":"to create a slightly more complex stunt scene,"},{"time":808000,"text":"and one of the most famous stunts is the one where James Bond"},{"time":811000,"text":"jumps off a dam in Switzerland and then is caught by a bungee."},{"time":816000,"text":"Got a very short clip here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"Yes, you can just about see it here."},{"time":824000,"text":"In this case, they were using a real stunt man. It was a very dangerous stunt."},{"time":827000,"text":"It was just voted, I think in the Sunday Times, as one of the most impressive stunts."},{"time":830000,"text":"Now, we've just tried and -- looked at our character and asked ourselves,"},{"time":833000,"text":"\"Can we do that ourselves as well?\""},{"time":835000,"text":"Can we use the physical simulation of the character,"},{"time":837000,"text":"use artificial intelligence,"},{"time":839000,"text":"put that artificial intelligence into the character,"},{"time":841000,"text":"drive virtual muscles, simulate the way he jumps off the dam,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and then skydive afterwards,"},{"time":847000,"text":"and have him caught by a bungee afterwards?"},{"time":849000,"text":"We did that. It took about altogether just two hours,"},{"time":852000,"text":"pretty much, to create the simulation."},{"time":854000,"text":"And that's what it looks like, here."},{"time":865000,"text":"Now, this could do with a bit more work. It's still very early stages,"},{"time":868000,"text":"and we pretty much just did this for a laugh,"},{"time":870000,"text":"just to see what we'd get out of it."},{"time":872000,"text":"But what we found over the past few months"},{"time":874000,"text":"is that this approach -- that we're pretty much standard upon --"},{"time":877000,"text":"is incredibly powerful."},{"time":879000,"text":"We are ourselves surprised what you actually get out of the simulations."},{"time":883000,"text":"There's very often very surprising behavior that you didn't predict before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"There's so many things we can do with this right now."},{"time":889000,"text":"The first thing, as I said, is going to be virtual stuntmen."},{"time":892000,"text":"Several studios are using this software now to produce virtual stuntmen,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and they're going to hit the screen quite soon, actually,"},{"time":898000,"text":"for some major productions."},{"time":900000,"text":"The second thing is video games."},{"time":903000,"text":"With this technology, video games will look different and they will feel very different."},{"time":907000,"text":"For the first time, you'll have actors that really feel very interactive,"},{"time":910000,"text":"that have real bodies that really react."},{"time":912000,"text":"I think that's going to be incredibly exciting."},{"time":915000,"text":"Probably starting with sports games,"},{"time":917000,"text":"which are going to become much more interactive."},{"time":919000,"text":"But I particularly am really excited"},{"time":920000,"text":"about using this technology in online worlds,"},{"time":923000,"text":"like there, for example, that Tom Melcher has shown us."},{"time":926000,"text":"The degree of interactivity you're going to get"},{"time":928000,"text":"is totally different, I think, from what you're getting right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"A third thing we are looking at and very interested in is simulation."},{"time":937000,"text":"We've been approached by several simulation companies,"},{"time":939000,"text":"but one project we're particularly excited about, which we're starting next month,"},{"time":942000,"text":"is to use our technology -- and in particular, the walking technology --"},{"time":946000,"text":"to help aid surgeons who work on children with cerebral palsy,"},{"time":950000,"text":"to predict the outcome of operations on these children."},{"time":953000,"text":"As you probably know,"},{"time":955000,"text":"it's very difficult to predict what the outcome of an operation is"},{"time":958000,"text":"if you try and correct the gait."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"The classic quote is, I think, it's unpredictable at best,"},{"time":963000,"text":"is what people think right now, is the outcome."},{"time":966000,"text":"Now, what we want to do with our software is allow our surgeons to have a tool."},{"time":970000,"text":"We're going to simulate the gait of a particular child"},{"time":973000,"text":"and the surgeon can then work on that simulation"},{"time":976000,"text":"and try out different ways to improve that gait,"},{"time":978000,"text":"before he actually commits to an actual surgery."},{"time":981000,"text":"That's one project we're particularly excited about,"},{"time":983000,"text":"and that's going to start next month."},{"time":987000,"text":"Just finally, this is only just the beginning."},{"time":990000,"text":"We can only do several behaviors right now."},{"time":992000,"text":"The AI isn't good enough to simulate a full human body."},{"time":995000,"text":"The body yes, but not all the motor skills that we have."},{"time":998000,"text":"And, I think, we're only there if we can have something like ballet dancing."},{"time":1001000,"text":"Right now, we don't have that"},{"time":1003000,"text":"but I'm very sure that we will be able to do that at some stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005000,"text":"We do have one unintentional dancer actually,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"the last thing I'm going to show you."},{"time":1010000,"text":"This was an AI contour that was produced and evolved --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"half-evolved, I should say -- to produce balance, basically."},{"time":1016000,"text":"So, you kick the guy and the guy's supposed to counter-balance."},{"time":1019000,"text":"That's what we thought was going to come out of this."},{"time":1022000,"text":"But this is what emerged out of it, in the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035000,"text":"Bizarrely, this thing doesn't have a head. I'm not quite sure why."},{"time":1039000,"text":"So, this was not something we actually put in there."},{"time":1041000,"text":"He just started to create that dance himself."},{"time":1045000,"text":"He's actually a better dancer than I am, I have to say."},{"time":1049000,"text":"And what you see after a while --"},{"time":1051000,"text":"I think he even goes into a climax right at the end."},{"time":1057000,"text":"And I think -- there you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062000,"text":"So, that all happened automatically. We didn't put that in there."},{"time":1064000,"text":"That's just the simulation creating this itself, basically."},{"time":1067000,"text":"So it's just --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070000,"text":"Thanks."},{"time":1073000,"text":"Not quite John Travolta yet, but we're working on that as well,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"so thanks very much for your time."},{"time":1078000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080000,"text":"CA: Incredible. That was really incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1082000,"text":"TR: Thanks."}]}]}